{"page":1,"results":[{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":1192541,"known_for_department":"Directing","name":"Katrine Philp","original_name":"Katrine Philp","popularity":0.0621,"profile_path":"/zLlLUU4v5viyLt1VTMQFt8Zveo0.jpg","known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/zmjm1tHCh0BYKOvZniaUqZQWv89.jpg","id":550668,"title":"False Confessions","original_title":"False Confessions","overview":"Defence attorney Jane Fisher-Byrialsen is determined to put an end to interrogation techniques that pressure innocent people into false confessions. The film follows four of her cases and examines the psychological aspect of how people end up confessing to crimes they have not committed and the consequences of these confessions – for those accused, for their families, and for society at large.","poster_path":"/svCjBSF78ldG6pxQpawuTCRDBnd.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[99],"popularity":0.0537,"release_date":"2018-03-17","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":8.0,"vote_count":5},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"id":209120,"title":"Dance for Me","original_title":"Dans for mig","overview":"14-year-old Mie is an elite dancer. When her partner stops dancing, her family decides to search for a new partner abroad. Russian Egor finds out that his mother has set up a try out for him, and if this turns out well, Egor will travel to Denmark. Since May 2011, he has lived with Mie and her parents in Denmark, where everything indicates that they are the perfect match on the dance floor. In Mie's home, however, problems are piling up. The family has suddenly gained a new member, and had it not been for the growing success, Egor would probably have been put on a plane back to his mum by now.","poster_path":"/9X0fRV0R7yrapDGkK4t9ZSjeywg.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[99],"popularity":0.0717,"release_date":"2012-11-14","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":7.6,"vote_count":5},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/znivEfN3tbxRubUARipG2SMWJhF.jpg","id":674884,"title":"Beautiful Something Left Behind","original_title":"Beautiful Something Left Behind","overview":"In New Jersey, the Good Grief community focuses on a holistic way of dealing with grief, where children can give in to rage in ‘the volcano room,' and say goodbye to a dying teddy bear patient in ‘the hospital room.'  Over the course of a year, we follow the weekly meetings and get close to Kimmy, Nicky, Peter, Nora, Nolan, and Mikayla and their close companion: grief. It is sometimes heartbreaking, but also humorous, to experience the questions about life and death through their open and curious minds.  Grief is high and heavy as a mountain, but it helps you understand what has happened, and that death is irreversible.","poster_path":"/uD7yfR9n61k79NJn7hRu782nAz8.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[99,18],"popularity":0.278,"release_date":"2020-03-16","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":9.0,"vote_count":4}]},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":1784714,"known_for_department":"Production","name":"Katrine Philp","original_name":"Katrine Philp","popularity":0.0143,"profile_path":null,"known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/9TkiBJ0kdIMS6oflS7rsaVDddjD.jpg","id":449239,"title":"Waiting for the Sun","original_title":"Waiting for the Sun","overview":"In China more people are on death row than the rest of the world combined. The children of the convicts are often left alone, stigmatized and living in the streets. Grandma Zhang, as the kids call her, is a former prison guard who has founded an orphanage in Nanzhao.","poster_path":"/jh4TewtzqO4WHAZRFgMXDOpDzYS.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[99],"popularity":0.2278,"release_date":"2017-03-19","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":6.2,"vote_count":5}]}],"total_pages":1,"total_results":2}